 537      // Strip Unicode control sequences: some apps like Telegram add a lot of them for unknown reasons             
 538      private String sanitizeUnicode(String orig) {                                                                 
 539          return orig.replaceAll("\\p{C}", "");                                                                     
 540      }                                                                                                             
 541                                                                                                                    
 542      private void dissectNotificationTo(Notification notification, NotificationSpec notificationSpec,              
 543                                         boolean preferBigText) {                                                   
 544                                                                                                                    
 545          Bundle extras = NotificationCompat.getExtras(notification);                                               
 546                                                                                                                    
 547          //dumpExtras(extras);                                                                                     
 548          if (extras == null) {                                                                                     
 549              return;                                                                                               
 550          }                                                                                                         
 551                                                                                                                    
 552          CharSequence title = extras.getCharSequence(Notification.EXTRA_TITLE);                                    
 553          if (title != null) {                                                                                      
 554              notificationSpec.title = sanitizeUnicode(title.toString());                                           
 555          }                                                                                                         
 556                                                                                                                    
 557          CharSequence contentCS = null;                                                                            
 558          if (preferBigText && extras.containsKey(Notification.EXTRA_BIG_TEXT)) {                                   
 559              contentCS = extras.getCharSequence(NotificationCompat.EXTRA_BIG_TEXT);                                
 560          } else if (extras.containsKey(Notification.EXTRA_TEXT)) {                                                 
 561              contentCS = extras.getCharSequence(NotificationCompat.EXTRA_TEXT);                                    
 562          }                                                                                                         
 563          if (contentCS != null) {                                                                                  
 564              notificationSpec.body = sanitizeUnicode(contentCS.toString());                                        
 565          }                                                                                                         
 566                                                                                                                    
 567      }

 569      private boolean isServiceRunning() {                                                                          
 570          ActivityManager manager = (ActivityManager) getSystemService(ACTIVITY_SERVICE);                           
 571          if (manager == null) {                                                                                    
 572              return false;                                                                                         
 573          }                                                                                                         
 574          for (ActivityManager.RunningServiceInfo service : manager.getRunningServices(Integer.MAX_VALUE)) {        
 575              if (DeviceCommunicationService.class.getName().equals(service.service.getClassName())) {              
 576                  return true;                                                                                      
 577              }                                                                                                     
 578          }                                                                                                         
 579          return false;                                                                                             





 580      }

 582      /**                                                                                                           
 583       * Try to handle media session notifications that tell info about the current play state.                     
 584       *                                                                                                            
 585       * @param mediaSession The mediasession to handle.                                                            
 586       * @return true if notification was handled, false otherwise                                                  
 587       */                                                                                                           
 588      public boolean handleMediaSessionNotification(MediaSessionCompat.Token mediaSession) {                        
 589          MusicSpec musicSpec = new MusicSpec();                                                                    
 590          MusicStateSpec stateSpec = new MusicStateSpec();                                                          
 591                                                                                                                    
 592          MediaControllerCompat c;                                                                                  
 593          try {                                                                                                     
 594              c = new MediaControllerCompat(getApplicationContext(), mediaSession);                                 
 595                                                                                                                    
 596              PlaybackStateCompat s = c.getPlaybackState();                                                         
 597              stateSpec.position = (int) (s.getPosition() / 1000);                                                  
 598              stateSpec.playRate = Math.round(100 * s.getPlaybackSpeed());                                          
 599              stateSpec.repeat = 1;                                                                                 
 600              stateSpec.shuffle = 1;                                                                                
 601              switch (s.getState()) {                                                                               
 602                  case PlaybackStateCompat.STATE_PLAYING:                                                           
 603                      stateSpec.state = MusicStateSpec.STATE_PLAYING;                                               
 604                      break;                                                                                        
 605                  case PlaybackStateCompat.STATE_STOPPED:                                                           
 606                      stateSpec.state = MusicStateSpec.STATE_STOPPED;                                               
 607                      break;                                                                                        
 608                  case PlaybackStateCompat.STATE_PAUSED:                                                            
 609                      stateSpec.state = MusicStateSpec.STATE_PAUSED;                                                
 610                      break;                                                                                        
 611                  default:                                                                                          
 612                      stateSpec.state = MusicStateSpec.STATE_UNKNOWN;                                               
 613                      break;                                                                                        
 614              }                                                                                                     
 615                                                                                                                    
 616              MediaMetadataCompat d = c.getMetadata();                                                              
 617              if (d == null)                                                                                        
 618                  return false;                                                                                     
 619              if (d.containsKey(MediaMetadata.METADATA_KEY_ARTIST))                                                 
 620                  musicSpec.artist = d.getString(MediaMetadataCompat.METADATA_KEY_ARTIST);                          
 621              if (d.containsKey(MediaMetadata.METADATA_KEY_ALBUM))                                                  
 622                  musicSpec.album = d.getString(MediaMetadataCompat.METADATA_KEY_ALBUM);                            
 623              if (d.containsKey(MediaMetadata.METADATA_KEY_TITLE))                                                  
 624                  musicSpec.track = d.getString(MediaMetadataCompat.METADATA_KEY_TITLE);                            
 625              if (d.containsKey(MediaMetadata.METADATA_KEY_DURATION))                                               
 626                  musicSpec.duration = (int) d.getLong(MediaMetadataCompat.METADATA_KEY_DURATION) / 1000;           
 627              if (d.containsKey(MediaMetadata.METADATA_KEY_NUM_TRACKS))                                             
 628                  musicSpec.trackCount = (int) d.getLong(MediaMetadataCompat.METADATA_KEY_NUM_TRACKS);              
 629              if (d.containsKey(MediaMetadata.METADATA_KEY_TRACK_NUMBER))                                           
 630                  musicSpec.trackNr = (int) d.getLong(MediaMetadataCompat.METADATA_KEY_TRACK_NUMBER);               
 631                                                                                                                    
 632              // finally, tell the device about it                                                                  
 633              GBApplication.deviceService().onSetMusicInfo(musicSpec);                                              
 634              GBApplication.deviceService().onSetMusicState(stateSpec);                                             
 635                                                                                                                    
 636              return true;                                                                                          
 637          } catch (NullPointerException | RemoteException e) {                                                      
 638              return false;                                                                                         
 639          }                                                                                                         
 640      }

 672              if (value == null) {                                                                                  
 673                  continue;                                                                                         
 674              }                                                                                                     
 675              LOG.debug(String.format("Notification extra: %s %s (%s)", key, value.toString(), value.getClass().getN🔵

 680      private boolean shouldIgnore(StatusBarNotification sbn) {                                                     

 681          /*                                                                                                        
 682           * return early if DeviceCommunicationService is not running,                                             
 683           * else the service would get started every time we get a notification.                                   
 684           * unfortunately we cannot enable/disable NotificationListener at runtime like we do with                 
 685           * broadcast receivers because it seems to invalidate the permissions that are                            
 686           * necessary for NotificationListenerService                                                              
 687           */                                                                                                       
 688          if (!isServiceRunning() || sbn == null) {                                                                 


 689              return true;                                                                                          
 690          }                                                                                                         
 691 -                                                                                                                  
 692          return shouldIgnoreSource(sbn.getPackageName()) || shouldIgnoreNotification(                              
 693                  sbn.getNotification(), sbn.getPackageName());                                                     
 694                                                                                                                    
 695      }

 697      private boolean shouldIgnoreSource(String source) {                                                           






 698          Prefs prefs = GBApplication.getPrefs();                                                                   
 699                                                                                                                    
 700          /* do not display messages from "android"                                                                 
 701           * This includes keyboard selection message, usb connection messages, etc                                 
 702           * Hope it does not filter out too much, we will see...                                                   
 703           */                                                                                                       
 704                                                                                                                    
 705          if (source.equals("android") ||                                                                           
 706                  source.equals("com.android.systemui") ||                                                          
 707                  source.equals("com.android.dialer") ||                                                            
 708                  source.equals("com.cyanogenmod.eleven")) {                                                        
 709              LOG.info("Ignoring notification, is a system event");                                                 
 710              return true;                                                                                          
 711          }                                                                                                         
 712                                                                                                                    
 713          if (source.equals("com.moez.QKSMS") ||                                                                    
 714                  source.equals("com.android.mms") ||                                                               
 715                  source.equals("com.sonyericsson.conversations") ||                                                
 716                  source.equals("com.android.messaging") ||

 765      /**                                                                                                           
 766       * Get the notification color that should be used for this Pebble notification.                               
 767       *                                                                                                            
 768       * Note that this method will *not* edit the NotificationSpec passed in. It will only evaluate the PebbleColor🔵
 769       *                                                                                                            
 770       * See Issue #815 on GitHub to see how notification colors are set.                                           
 771       *                                                                                                            
 772       * @param notificationSpec The NotificationSpec to read from.                                                 
 773       * @return Returns a PebbleColor that best represents this notification.                                      
 774       */                                                                                                           
 775      private byte getPebbleColorForNotification(NotificationSpec notificationSpec) {                               
 776          String appId = notificationSpec.sourceAppId;                                                              
 777          NotificationType existingType = notificationSpec.type;                                                    
 778                                                                                                                    
 779          // If the notification type is known, return the associated color.                                        
 780          if (existingType != NotificationType.UNKNOWN) {                                                           
 781              return existingType.color;                                                                            
 782          }                                                                                                         
 783                                                                                                                    
 784          // Otherwise, we go and attempt to find the color from the app icon.                                      
 785          Drawable icon;                                                                                            
 786          try {                                                                                                     
 787              icon = getApplicationContext().getPackageManager().getApplicationIcon(appId);                         
 788              Objects.requireNonNull(icon);                                                                         
 789          } catch (Exception ex) {                                                                                  
 790              // If we can't get the icon, we go with the default defined above.                                    
 791              LOG.warn("Could not get icon for AppID " + appId, ex);                                                
 792              return PebbleColor.IslamicGreen;                                                                      
 793          }                                                                                                         
 794                                                                                                                    
 795          Bitmap bitmapIcon = BitmapUtil.convertDrawableToBitmap(icon);                                             
 796          int iconPrimaryColor = new Palette.Builder(bitmapIcon)                                                    
 797                  .generate()                                                                                       
 798                  .getVibrantColor(Color.parseColor("#aa0000"));                                                    
 799                                                                                                                    
 800          return PebbleUtils.getPebbleColor(iconPrimaryColor);                                                      
 801      }

 162                  case ACTION_MUTE:

 165                          LOG.info("could not lookup handle for mute action");                                      
 166                          break;

 168

 171                      break;                                                                                        
 172                  case ACTION_DISMISS: {                                                                            
 173                      StatusBarNotification[] sbns = NotificationListener.this.getActiveNotifications();            
 174                      Long ts = (Long) mNotificationHandleLookup.lookup(handle);                                    
 175                      if (ts == null) {

 177                          break;

 538      boolean shouldContinueAfterFilter(@NonNull String body, @NonNull List<String> wordsList, @NonNull Notification🔵
 539                                                                                                                    
 540          LOG.debug("Mode: '{}' Submode: '{}' WordsList: '{}'", notificationFilter.getNotificationFilterMode(), noti🔵
 541                                                                                                                    
 542          boolean allMode = notificationFilter.getNotificationFilterSubMode() == NOTIFICATION_FILTER_SUBMODE_ALL;   
 543                                                                                                                    
 544          switch (notificationFilter.getNotificationFilterMode()) {                                                 
 545              case NOTIFICATION_FILTER_MODE_BLACKLIST:                                                              
 546                  if (allMode) {                                                                                    
 547                      for (String word : wordsList) {                                                               
 548                          if (!body.contains(word)) {                                                               
 549                              LOG.info("Not every word was found, blacklist has no effect, processing continues."); 
 550                              return true;                                                                          
 551                          }                                                                                         
 552                      }                                                                                             
 553                      LOG.info("Every word was found, blacklist has effect, processing stops.");                    
 554                      return false;                                                                                 
 555                  } else {                                                                                          
 556                      boolean containsAny = StringUtils.containsAny(body, wordsList.toArray(new CharSequence[0]));  
 557                      if (!containsAny) {                                                                           
 558                          LOG.info("No matching word was found, blacklist has no effect, processing continues.");   
 559                      } else {                                                                                      
 560                          LOG.info("At least one matching word was found, blacklist has effect, processing stops.");
 561                      }                                                                                             
 562                      return !containsAny;                                                                          
 563                  }                                                                                                 
 564                                                                                                                    
 565              case NOTIFICATION_FILTER_MODE_WHITELIST:                                                              
 566                  if (allMode) {                                                                                    
 567                      for (String word : wordsList) {                                                               
 568                          if (!body.contains(word)) {                                                               
 569                              LOG.info("Not every word was found, whitelist has no effect, processing stops.");     
 570                              return false;                                                                         
 571                          }                                                                                         
 572                      }                                                                                             
 573                      LOG.info("Every word was found, whitelist has effect, processing continues.");                
 574                      return true;                                                                                  
 575                  } else {                                                                                          
 576                      boolean containsAny = StringUtils.containsAny(body, wordsList.toArray(new CharSequence[0]));  
 577                      if (containsAny) {                                                                            
 578                          LOG.info("At least one matching word was found, whitelist has effect, processing continues🔵
 579                      } else {                                                                                      
 580                          LOG.info("No matching word was found, whitelist has no effect, processing stops.");       
 581                      }                                                                                             
 582                      return containsAny;                                                                           
 583                  }                                                                                                 
 584                                                                                                                    
 585              default:                                                                                              
 586                  return true;                                                                                      
 587          }                                                                                                         
 588      }

 597

 614              contentCS = extras.getCharSequence(NotificationCompat.EXTRA_TEXT);

 616          if (contentCS != null) {

 618          }

 869      private byte getPebbleColorForNotification(NotificationSpec notificationSpec) {                               
 870          String appId = notificationSpec.sourceAppId;                                                              
 871          NotificationType existingType = notificationSpec.type;                                                    
 872                                                                                                                    
 873          // If the notification type is known, return the associated color.                                        
 874          if (existingType != NotificationType.UNKNOWN) {                                                           
 875              return existingType.color;                                                                            
 876          }                                                                                                         
 877                                                                                                                    
 878          // Otherwise, we go and attempt to find the color from the app icon.                                      
 879          Drawable icon;                                                                                            
 880          try {                                                                                                     
 881              icon = getApplicationContext().getPackageManager().getApplicationIcon(appId);                         
 882              Objects.requireNonNull(icon);                                                                         
 883          } catch (Exception ex) {                                                                                  
 884              // If we can't get the icon, we go with the default defined above.                                    
 885              LOG.warn("Could not get icon for AppID " + appId, ex);                                                
 886              return PebbleColor.IslamicGreen;                                                                      
 887          }                                                                                                         
 888                                                                                                                    
 889          Bitmap bitmapIcon = BitmapUtil.convertDrawableToBitmap(icon);                                             
 890          int iconPrimaryColor = new Palette.Builder(bitmapIcon)                                                    
 891                  .generate()                                                                                       
 892                  .getVibrantColor(Color.parseColor("#aa0000"));                                                    
 893                                                                                                                    
 894          return PebbleUtils.getPebbleColor(iconPrimaryColor);                                                      
 895      }                                                                                                             
 896  }
